snippet.textDisplay: I don't know what my relationship with the soil with Assam is but it is unbreakable.... gatekeepers stay away..
snippet.textOriginal: I don't know what my relationship with the soil with Assam is but it is unbreakable.... gatekeepers stay away..

snippet.textDisplay:
My dad's family is from Punjab and my mum's family is from Andhra but I was born and brought up in Assam and now settled in Assam itself, I've always recognized Assam as my motherland it gave me a feeling of home, I love the culture, cuisine and simple people of Assam, 

If you are someone coming from a diverse family then you probably know how difficult it becomes for people like us to find a real home cuz we don't look native but for me I was always lucky that I was born in Assam, and able to speak Assamese and ever since that I've always said that I'm from Assam proudly.

Our country is just amazing with such a rich culture and diversity, and I'll always say proudly that Assam is a rich part of it!  Joi Aai Axom !!!
